      "writtenOn": "2019-07-09T04:34:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is new. It is needed when running luciexe locally with developer credentials. In this case luciexe itself hosts LUCI_CONTEXT[\"local_auth\"] server, and it needs git-scoped refresh token to make git credential helper work.\n\nOn Swarming, LUCI_CONTEXT[\"local_auth\"] is hosted by Swarming bot and it supports tokens with arbitrary list of scopes already. git credential helper contacts the local auth server directly bypassing luciexe layer (so it doesn\u0027t matter what scopes we specify in luciexe).",
